[
  {
    "task": "Provide a note on reserves for the last four years",
    "owner": "HEFCW",
    "deadline": "none",
    "evidence": "Lynne Neagle AM: You did say that you would give the committee a note on reserves for the last four years,"
  },
  {
    "task": "Send a transcript to check for accuracy following the meeting",
    "owner": "HEFCW",
    "deadline": "none",
    "evidence": "Lynne Neagle AM: And, as usual, you'll be sent a transcript to check for accuracy following the meeting."
  },
  {
    "task": "Increase QR funding in real terms",
    "owner": "HEFCW",
    "deadline": "none",
    "evidence": "Sian Gwenllian AM: Have you carried out any kind of assessment of the impact of this level of research funding on universities and, indeed, on the Welsh economy?"
  },
  {
    "task": "Maintain the attractiveness of Welsh universities to students",
    "owner": "HEFCW",
    "deadline": "none",
    "evidence": "Bethan Owen: And, just to add, I think the key bit of that is maintaining the attractiveness of Welsh universities to students, because a large proportion are coming not from just Wales, but from England and internationally—so, that's a key part—and also that our research portfolio is invested in, and that also brings economic benefits."
  },
  {
    "task": "Increase openness and transparency around the use of fee income",
    "owner": "HEFCW",
    "deadline": "none",
    "evidence": "Janet Finch-Saunders AM: The council's remit letter for the 2019-20 academic year from the Minister does ask you to consider how you'd increase openness and transparency around the use of fee income."
  },
  {
    "task": "Support and fund growth in part-time provision",
    "owner": "HEFCW",
    "deadline": "none",
    "evidence": "Hefin David AM: Part-time student numbers are bucking the trend in Wales, as I understand it, and we are seeing a bigger increase in Wales of part-time numbers than elsewhere in the UK. How is that going to be sustainable within current arrangements?"
  },
  {
    "task": "Place funding back into the system for innovation",
    "owner": "HEFCW",
    "deadline": "2020-21",
    "evidence": "Bethan Owen: One aspect that we do intend to fund—and this is from Diamond, as well as Reid—is to place funding back into the system for innovation. We're consulting currently, with the intention, if the funding is available to us, clearly, in the year 2020-21, to provide £15 million back into the sector in innovation funding."
  },
  {
    "task": "Provide £15 million in innovation funding to support universities in accessing UKRI funding",
    "owner": "HEFCW",
    "deadline": "2020-21",
    "evidence": "Bethan Owen: That £15 million will be money that comes from us, but the intention is that the money will go in in order to improve universities' ability to access that funding from UKRI."
  }
]

